   "source": [
    "# Analysing Trends and Factors in Female Labor Force Participation in Agriculture\n",
    "\n",
    "# Collaborated with a team to collect and analyse data from sources like the World Bank and UN Women to gain insights into trends in female labour force participation in agriculture.\n",
    "# Examined various factors such as education, wage rates, GDP, birth rates, marriage age, and more to understand their impact on the female labour force in agriculture.\n",
    "# Investigated how different factors play distinct roles in female labour force participation across countries, with a focus on India, China, and the USA.\n",
    "# Identified and highlighted missing data points related to factors like menstrual equity, access to menstrual products, and healthcare access for reproductive procedures.\n",
    "# Employed data cleaning techniques to tidy up data, identify structures, select relevant portions, address missing data, and remove noise.\n",
    "# Organized data from diverse sources like the World Bank and UN to ensure compatibility and uniformity.\n",
    "# Conducted descriptive analysis, summarizing key variables, exploring possible correlations, and considering the natural structure of the data, all while justifying analytical choices and methodologies.\n",
    "# Employed data modelling techniques, including linear regression and neural network modes.\n",
    "# Compared the results of different models to assess their fit and the veracity of results, identifying key response and predictor variables to answer research questions.\n",
    "# Discussed assumptions and the quality of the linear regression model, ensuring a critical examination of the analytical approach.\n",
    "# Provided interpretations and conclusions, critically reflecting on the research outcomes and the validity of the investigation, while acknowledging any limitations.\n"
   ]
  },
